{"questionId":"35020459","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Jae Hee plays a game involving a biased six-sided die.</p>\n<p>The faces of the die are labelled −3, −1, 0, 1, 2 and 5.</p>\n<p>The score for the game, <em>X</em>, is the number which lands face up after the die is rolled.</p>\n<p>The following table shows the probability distribution for <em>X</em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/e7993ef273dec0f949b26b0a687fd76f1ecb7de5.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the exact value of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p\">\n  <mi>p</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{4}{{18}}\\left( {\\frac{2}{9}} \\right)\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>18</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n        <mn>9</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"35020459","referenceCode":"SPM.1.SL.TZ0.12a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the exact value of p .","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive, conditional, independence, prob diagrams","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.7—Discrete random variables"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}